Apply configuration changes to the environment.

Sync compares the current configuration (weg.toml or pyproject.toml)
against the recorded state and applies any differences:

  - Installs new apps
  - Removes deleted apps
  - Updates changed app versions
  - Creates new sites
  - Removes deleted sites

By default, sync will show a preview of changes and ask for confirmation.

Examples:
  weg sync           # Interactive sync with confirmation
  weg sync -y        # Apply changes without confirmation
  weg sync --dry-run # Preview changes without applying

Usage:
  weg sync [flags]

Flags:
      --dry-run   Preview changes without applying
  -h, --help      help for sync

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts
